  "narrative_arc": "Wakes up as a giant insect. Kafka documents the economic and social consequences with bureaucratic precision — the missed work, the family's financial ruin, the shrinking room, the family's transformation from dependence to revulsion to abandonment. The metamorphosis is disability rendered as genre.",
  "why_this_character_matters": "Gregor is disability as architecture. His dome maps what happens when a provider becomes a dependent — every layer inverts. Layer 6 (Economic) collapses, Layer 5 (Housing) contracts to a single room, Layer 8 (Community) shrinks to one sister and then to nobody.",
